{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place flour, salt and butter into mixing bowl and mix <b>4 sec\/speed 6<b>. Add water and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer dough to a floured work surface or silicone mat and roll into a rectangle (approx. ¼ in. thick). Refrigerate pastry while making filling. Clean mixing bowl.","Place onions into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add bacon and chorizo into mixing bowl, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <b>10 min\/250°F\/speed 1<b>.","Add butternut squash, syrup, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and chili flakes and cook <b>15 min\/212°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer filling to 4 large ramekins or mini casseroles (approx. 8 oz ea.) and allow to cool to room temperature before applying dough. Meanwhile set oven rack to the middle position and preheat to 400°F.","Cut chilled pastry into strips and lay strips over cooled pie filling. Trim any overhanging pastry, if needed. Seal edges by pressing onto sides of ramekins with fingertips or a fork. With a cookie cutter, cut out decorative shapes from remaining pastry and use to garnish pies. In a small bowl, use a fork to whisk together egg and water and brush pastry with egg wash.","Place Savory Butternut Squash Pies onto a foil lined baking sheet and bake for 45-55 minutes (400°F). Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["7 oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","¼ tsp salt","6 oz unsalted butter, cold, diced (¼ in.)","2 oz ice water","6 oz yellow onions, halved","8 oz bacon, diced","8 oz Mexican chorizo, casings removed, in pieces","30 oz butternut squash, peeled, de-seeded, cubed (1 in.)","2 oz maple syrup","½ tsp ground cinnamon","1 tsp ground ginger","½ tsp ground nutmeg","1 pinch dried red chili flakes","1 large egg","1 tsp water"]}],"id":"r402485","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-16hIII1Hkzk\/XZQGTlzGC6I\/AAAAAAAAb8k\/-GuFOUijY9Q3exbUZSVC2BL0sq800W0rQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_MrUwKllwN8JdqXSM.png"